race.comment: Most of these getting to 2000m for the first time. THE MEAN FIDDLER (4) looks one of the more likely types to relish the trip. He's a son of Highland Reel who bolted in on debut, trying hard behind a well ridden winner at Sandown Lakeside last time in Flying Done, who won here last week, beating OUR CHIEF (3). OUR CHIEF was well backed there but the leader just had it too easy (again) and he had to settle for second. 2000m looks okay for him too. WRIGLEY FIELD (1) started $3 behind Flying Done & THE MEAN FIDDLER at Sandown and just got too far back in the small field there. He should appreciate this trip now. HELIOSON (8) struggled behind Flying Done last time but is another that will relish the extra ground.
